HEADWORD: Wonted
<hw>Wont"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Accustomed; customary;
usual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Again his <qex>wonted</qex> weapon proved.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like an old piece of furniture left alone in its <qex>wonted</qex>
corner.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She was <qex>wonted</qex> to the place, and would not remove.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wontedness</ent>⟦br⟧
